<DATELINE>
   TORONTO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Canada yesterday sharply cut tobacco taxes in the hope of curbing the growth
in cigarette smuggling across its border with the US, Bernard Simon writes
from Toronto.
The measures announced yesterday include a CDollars 5 tax cut per carton of
cigarettes, bringing federal taxes down to CDollars 11 a carton.
