<TEXT>
Disappointed liquidation hit COCOA futures prices at the London Commodity
Exchange yesterday after early buying failed to achieve the breach of
resistance around Pounds 900 a tonne for May delivery. By the close the
price had surrendered all but Pounds 5 of Friday's Pounds 23 rise to close
at Pounds 872 a tonne.
But COFFEE prices maintained their rally with a Dollars 13 rise to Dollars
1,212 a tonne.
As speculative interest slackened base metals prices generally succumbed to
profit-taking at the London Metal Exchange.
