been reluctant to accept Daishowa's restructuring plan until it removed the
family's influence. Daishowa's investments grew rapidly during the 1980s
under Mr Ryoei Saito, the controversial honorary chairman.
Daishowa has been trying to work out a rehabilitation plan acceptable to its
creditors.
