<HEADLINE>
FT  08 FEB 94 / International Company News: Telecom posts record NZDollars
134.6m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TERRY HALL
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WELLINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Telecom, the New Zealand utility controlled by Bell Atlantic and Ameritech,
reported record third-quarter earnings of NZDollars 134.6m (USDollars 77m),
an 8.9 per cent lift on the NZDollars 123.6m achieved in the same period
last year.
The improvement pushed Telecom's net earnings for the nine months to
December 31 up to NZDollars 386m, a 15.3 per cent increase on the NZDollars
224.7m earned in the same period of last year.
Mr Jeff White, chief financial officer, said the company was well on the way
to achieving another record profit for the full year. Mr Roderick Deane,
chief executive, told a news conference: 'It was a very satisfactory
quarter, reflecting growth in the business, systems advances and market
retention.' Per-share earnings for the third quarter rose to NZDollars 5.7
cents from 5.2 cents, and earnings per share for the nine months rose to
16.3 cents from 14.2 cents.
Third-quarter operating revenue rose by 1.6 per cent to NZDollars 634.6m.
Telecom executives said this reflected strong growth in core markets as well
as a continued rise in revenues from cellular services, directories and new
network services.
Volumes in the national call market climbed 10.1 per cent while growth in
international calls was up 15.7 per cent.
