FT  08 FEB 94 / Observer: Fat tome
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
One big problem faces Finland's new president, Martti Ahtisaari - will he be
able to use the recently built library in the new official presidential
residence in Helsinki?
The library's architect obviously subscribes to the myth that all Finns are
slimline, thanks to their predilection for winter sports. The spiral
stairway to the library's top floor is correspondingly narrow.
But the amply proportioned Ahtisaari admits that the only form of sport he
enjoys is taking a sauna. Will he be able to squeeze his way up the stairs?
Ahtisaari thinks he will - so as long as he takes a deep breath.
But which state president has time for reading anyway?
