FT  08 FEB 94 / Management (The Growing Business): UK bank support for
franchising - In a Nutshell
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
European companies seeking bank support for franchising operations are
likely to get the warmest and most knowledgeable reception in the UK and the
Netherlands, according to a study.
Elsewhere, banks have a poor knowledge of franchising and little interest in
developing its potential.
The study* is by Professor John Stanworth of the University of Westminster
and Peter Stern, franchise manager at NatWest Bank.
*Improving small business survival rates via franchising - University of
Westminster. Tel 071 911 5000.
</TEXT>
