FT  08 FEB 94 / Review of counties' future extended
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Up to six weeks longer is to be allowed for the first stages of most of the
review of local government in the English counties, the Local Government
Commission for England said yesterday.
The decision follows the government's announcement that it would not appeal
against the recent High Court ruling that Mr John Gummer, the environment
secretary, had acted unlawfully in calling for the two-tier structure of
county and district councils to be abandoned in all but 'exceptional'
circumstances.
The government said some councils had asked the commission for more time to
consider their positions because they felt the change of guidance might
alter the nature of the submissions they were planning to send to the
commission.
