</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GRAHAM
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
In a weekend referendum, almost 56 per cent of voters rejected a proposal to
separate the industrial town of Mestre from the Venice administration,
writes Robert Graham. It was the third abortive attempt since 1979 to force
a divorce.
