<HEADLINE>
FT  08 FEB 94 / Car sales recover in January
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KEVIN DONE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
West European new car sales rose by 6.3 per cent to 1.029m in January
compared with the same month in 1993, according to provisional figures from
the European Automobile Manufacturers Association, writes Kevin Done.
The increase ends 12 successive monthly declines, but the scale of recovery
remains modest since sales in January 1993 were very depressed, having
fallen 23 per cent from the previous year. Sales fell by an estimated 15.2
per cent in the whole of 1993 to 11.45m. Most industry forecasts suggest a
1-2 per cent recovery this year.
</TEXT>
